From: Kairo Authors <kairo@research>
Date: Wed Jun 24 15:00:00 2026 +0000
Subject: [RFC/POC] 0025: fairness accounting and sysfs visibility

RFC/POC — Not for LKML submission.

Wire Stage 12 fairness counters into sysfs boilerplate and add
store/show functions for tunables.

Stage 12 introduced the fairness data structures and conceptual hooks
(kairo_fairness_allow_decode, kairo_fairness_throttle_prefetch, etc.)
but left sysfs as scaffold comments only. The repo stated:

  Fairness sysfs counters are scaffolded but not wired in sysfs
  boilerplate.
  Fairness sysfs tunables are scaffolded but not wired in sysfs
  boilerplate.

Patch 0025 fixes this by adding:

Sysfs tunables (read/write):
  kairo_fairness_enable          0=disabled, 1=enabled
  kairo_model_decode_credit      per-model credit pool (1..100000)
  kairo_session_decode_credit    per-session credit pool (1..100000)
  kairo_fairness_refill_ms       refill interval in ms (1..60000)
  kairo_noisy_session_threshold  decode dispatch threshold (1..1000000)

Sysfs counters (read-only):
  kairo_fairness_refills
  kairo_fairness_model_throttles
  kairo_fairness_session_throttles
  kairo_noisy_session_events
  kairo_protected_decode_dispatches
  kairo_prefetch_fairness_throttles
  kairo_write_fairness_demotions

Accounting: counters are wired into the Stage 12 fairness hooks.
Each event observation increments the corresponding counter exactly
once. No double-counting per request.

LINUX-6.8-CHECK: Sysfs show/store functions follow the mq-deadline
DD_RO_ATTR / DD_ATTR pattern established in foundation patch 0004.

Signed-off-by: Kairo Authors <kairo@research>
